ADVANCED USER LAYER (Precision Without Losing Discipline)
1. Adjustable Discipline Strictness (CRITICAL)
Problem

Advanced users will resist fixed friction and rigid gating.

Solution

Introduce a Discipline Profile System

Modes:
Strict Mode (default)
Hard rules = absolute
Full friction on override
Balanced Mode
Some hard rules can degrade into “soft-block” (warning but executable)
Reduced timer
Expert Mode
All rules enforce scoring, not blocking
Overrides still logged + penalized
No timer, but mandatory justification remains
TRD Addition
DisciplineProfile {
  mode: "strict" | "balanced" | "expert"
  overrideFrictionLevel: number
  hardRuleEnforcement: "block" | "warn"
}
UX

Settings → “Discipline Level”

Slider or 3-state toggle
Visual explanation:
“Strict = maximum enforcement”
“Expert = full flexibility, full accountability”
2. Strategy Variants & Branching
Problem

Advanced users iterate constantly.

Solution

Allow branching strategies like version control

Feature:
“Clone & Modify Strategy”
Track lineage:
Growth Breakout v1 → v2 → v2.1
TRD Addition
Strategy {
  parentStrategyId?: string
  changeLog: string[]
}
UX

Strategy Page:

“Branch Strategy” button
Timeline view of versions
3. Multi-Strategy Parallel Scoring
Problem

Advanced traders think in multiple lenses simultaneously.

Solution

Allow:

One ticker → scored against multiple strategies simultaneously

UX

